- ♪ I GOT THE BEAT,
SO ALL THE KIDS DANCE WITH ME ♪

00:03.420 --> 00:05.046
♪ ME, ME, ME ♪

00:05.130 --> 00:06.881
♪ PICK IT UP AND TURN AROUND,
HERE COMES MIGHTY B ♪

00:06.965 --> 00:08.550
♪ BEE, BEE, BEE ♪

00:08.633 --> 00:12.429
♪ ♪

00:12.512 --> 00:14.139
♪ MIGHTY ♪
- ♪ LA, LA, HEY ♪

00:14.222 --> 00:16.056
- ♪ MIGHTY ♪
- ♪ LA, LA, WOW ♪

00:16.140 --> 00:18.059
- ♪ COME ON, EVERYBODY,
MIGHTY B ♪

00:18.143 --> 00:20.145
♪ I GOT THE BEAT,
SO ALL THE KIDS DANCE WITH ME ♪

00:20.228 --> 00:21.688
♪ ME, ME, ME ♪

00:21.771 --> 00:23.690
♪ STICK 'EM UP ALL AROUND,
HERE COMES MIGHTY B ♪

00:23.773 --> 00:24.357
♪ BEE, BEE, BEE ♪

00:24.441 --> 00:28.027
♪ ♪

00:28.111 --> 00:31.281
♪ COME ON, EVERYBODY,
MIGHTY B ♪

00:31.364 --> 00:33.324
♪ MIGHTY, MIGHTY B ♪

00:37.162 --> 00:40.123
[quirky synthesizer music]

00:40.206 --> 00:45.211
♪ ♪

00:47.630 --> 00:50.675
[both grunting]

00:53.011 --> 00:54.721
- AH, MAGNETS ARE LAME.

00:54.804 --> 00:55.722
THEY'RE, LIKE, TOTES CLINGY.

00:55.805 --> 00:58.558
- YEAH, LIKE MOTORS, MAGNETS?

00:58.641 --> 01:00.560
I'M NOT FEELING THIS BADGE.

01:00.643 --> 01:03.855
I MEAN,
WHO EVEN LIKES MOTORS?

01:04.855 --> 01:07.108
- HELLO, HONEYBEES.

01:09.360 --> 01:11.154
HEAR THAT ENGINE PURR?

01:11.237 --> 01:13.239
AH, I WAS GONNA BUILD A ROBOT,

01:13.323 --> 01:15.992
BUT I FIGURED IT ONLY TAKES
36 HOURS TO MAKE A SCOOTER.

01:16.075 --> 01:19.204
- YOU <i> WOULD</i> KNOW THAT, MISSY.

01:19.287 --> 01:21.080
YOU, LIKE, ARE A ROBOT.

01:21.164 --> 01:23.750
[both laughing]

01:23.833 --> 01:26.002
- DO YOU REALLY THINK
I'M A ROBOT?

01:26.085 --> 01:27.921
[both laughing]
WHAT?

01:29.964 --> 01:32.091
- OH, YEAH.
THINK ABOUT IT.

01:32.175 --> 01:32.759
YOU NEVER BREAK THE RULES.

01:32.842 --> 01:34.719
YOU NEVER GET TIRED.

01:34.803 --> 01:36.304
AND YOU HAVE NO STYLE.

01:37.430 --> 01:39.265
- HMM, YES, I DO LOVE RULES.

01:39.349 --> 01:40.558
I AM INEXHAUSTIBLE.

01:40.642 --> 01:43.061
AND FASHION TRENDS DO
OFTEN PASS ME BY.

01:43.144 --> 01:45.104
- AND LOOK:
YOU ATTRACT MAGNETS.

01:49.526 --> 01:51.986
- [grunting]

01:52.070 --> 01:53.613
OOH!

01:53.696 --> 01:56.115
- SEE? YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW
YOUR OWN STRENGTH.

01:56.199 --> 01:59.035
THAT'S TOTES ROBO.

01:59.118 --> 02:00.411
OW!

02:00.495 --> 02:02.080
LET GO, MACHINE GIRL.

02:02.163 --> 02:03.248
[chuckles]

02:03.331 --> 02:04.415
- WHOA.

02:04.499 --> 02:07.627
AM I REALLY A ROBOT?

02:07.710 --> 02:09.711
PROCESSING, PROCESSING.

02:09.795 --> 02:11.381
NEED MORE DATA.

02:11.464 --> 02:14.217
MUST EXIT
WITHOUT BENDING MY KNEES.

02:14.300 --> 02:17.262
[both laugh]

02:20.014 --> 02:22.725
- UM, HOW MUCH LONGER
DO I HAVE TO STAND LIKE THIS?

02:22.809 --> 02:24.435
- [grunts]

02:27.647 --> 02:29.566
- [sighs]

02:29.649 --> 02:30.608
- GENTLEMEN, I AM SORRY

02:30.692 --> 02:33.027
TO INTERRUPT
YOUR ARTISTIC PROCESS,

02:33.111 --> 02:36.948
BUT EVIDENCE HAS COME TO LIGHT
SUGGESTING THAT I AM...

02:37.031 --> 02:38.658
A ROBOT.

02:38.741 --> 02:39.701
[both laugh]

02:39.784 --> 02:41.161
A ROBOT?

02:41.244 --> 02:42.245
- YES.

02:42.328 --> 02:44.122
I'VE ALWAYS ACCEPTED
THE POSSIBILITY

02:44.205 --> 02:47.458
THAT I MAY BE A ROBOT, ANDROID,
AND/OR REPLICANT.

02:47.542 --> 02:50.169
AND TO ANSWER THIS QUESTION
ONCE AND FOR ALL,

02:50.253 --> 02:53.840
I NEED YOU TO ADMINISTER
THIS FOOLPROOF ROBOT TEST.

02:53.923 --> 02:56.009
- BUT YOU'RE NOT A ROBOT.

02:56.092 --> 02:57.760
YOU DON'T EVEN LOOK
LIKE A ROBOT.

02:57.844 --> 03:00.263
- OBVIOUSLY IF I AM A ROBOT,

03:00.346 --> 03:03.641
I'M AN ADVANCED MODEL
WHO LOOKS 100% HUMAN.

03:03.725 --> 03:05.351
COME ON, BEN.

03:05.435 --> 03:06.769
- UH, YOU'RE RIGHT.

03:06.853 --> 03:08.396
WHAT ELSE AM I DOING
THIS AFTERNOON?

03:08.479 --> 03:13.443
"A TRUE ROBOT CAN DISASSEMBLE
AND REASSEMBLE

03:13.526 --> 03:15.778
A COMPUTER BLINDFOLDED."

03:15.862 --> 03:16.696
- DONE.

03:16.779 --> 03:19.073
- HMM.
GUESS YOU ARE A ROBOT.

03:19.157 --> 03:20.241
ARE WE DONE NOW?

03:20.325 --> 03:22.702
- OH, BEN, I WISH
TO SETTLE THE ISSUE.

03:22.785 --> 03:23.536
BUT COME ON.

03:23.620 --> 03:24.829
IF YOU CAN TIE YOUR SHOELACES,

03:24.913 --> 03:26.873
YOU CAN REBUILD A COMPUTER.

03:26.956 --> 03:29.208
WE NEED MORE TESTS.

03:29.292 --> 03:30.376
[thunder rolls]

03:30.460 --> 03:32.795
- "A TRUE ROBOT IS ALWAYS
THE FIRST TARGET

03:32.879 --> 03:36.507
STRUCK BY LIGHTNING"?

03:39.552 --> 03:41.471
- WAIT.

03:41.554 --> 03:43.348
THE RUBBER SKIN
OVER MY METAL FRAME

03:43.431 --> 03:45.224
COULD BE DEFLECTING
THE VOLTS.

03:45.308 --> 03:49.437
- NEXT, "TRUE ROBOTS
CAN'T FEEL PAIN."

03:49.520 --> 03:50.897
- DO IT, HAPPY.

03:53.816 --> 03:57.445
C3POW! OW!

03:57.528 --> 04:00.073
[throbbing]

04:00.156 --> 04:01.991
THAT WAS FOR THE LIGHTNING,
WASN'T IT?

04:02.075 --> 04:04.160
- [chuckles]

04:04.243 --> 04:06.245
- OKAY, SO THAT HURT.

04:06.329 --> 04:08.957
- UH, HOW ABOUT WE TRY
THIS TEST?

04:09.040 --> 04:11.626
"A TRUE ROBOT
CAN'T DEFINE LOVE."

04:11.709 --> 04:12.335
GO.

04:12.418 --> 04:14.712
- WELL, UM, LOVE IS...

04:14.796 --> 04:16.214
YOU KNOW, IT'S COMPLICATED.

04:16.297 --> 04:20.134
AND, UH, I KNOW THAT
IT'S A MANY-SPLENDORED THING.

04:20.218 --> 04:22.679
UH, ALL YOU NEED IS LOVE?

04:22.762 --> 04:24.681
IT MEANS NEVER BEING SORRY.

04:24.764 --> 04:27.600
UM, IT'S A FIERY RING...

04:27.684 --> 04:30.520
OH, OH, IT'S ON
THE TIP OF MY TONGUE.

04:30.603 --> 04:33.648
UH...UH...

04:33.731 --> 04:35.775
I CAN'T DEFINE LOVE!

04:35.858 --> 04:38.069
I MUST BE 100% ROBOT!

04:38.987 --> 04:40.780
- YEAH, SURE, THAT'S IT.

04:42.115 --> 04:44.659
- [sighs]
SO MANY QUESTIONS:

04:44.742 --> 04:46.035
WHO MADE ME?

04:46.119 --> 04:47.662
WHAT KIND OF BATTERIES
DO I RUN ON?

04:47.745 --> 04:48.746
AM I COMPATIBLE WITH MY LAPTOP?

04:48.830 --> 04:50.915
AM I USER FRIENDLY
OR USER UNFRIENDLY?

04:50.999 --> 04:53.209
AND MOST IMPORTANTLY:

04:53.293 --> 04:56.254
WHAT AWESOME STUFF CAN I DO?

04:56.337 --> 04:57.296
screech!

04:57.380 --> 04:59.132
1001101?

04:59.716 --> 05:02.093
THANK YOU.

05:05.805 --> 05:07.682
[cat yowls]

05:10.476 --> 05:11.310
[growls]

05:14.188 --> 05:15.690
[screeches]

05:18.067 --> 05:18.985
- COOL.

05:19.068 --> 05:20.486
I EVEN HAVE
SCRATCH-RESISTANT SKIN.

05:22.488 --> 05:24.115
DON'T THANK ME, CANINE.

05:24.198 --> 05:25.992
THANK MY PROGRAMMING.

05:26.075 --> 05:26.534
HA HA HA.

05:29.454 --> 05:31.456
- THAT IS MY TOAST,
YOU STUPID TOASTER!

05:35.168 --> 05:36.210
- CITIZEN, CEASE AND DESIST

05:36.294 --> 05:39.922
THIS HOSTILITY
TOWARD MY ROBOT BROTHER.

05:40.006 --> 05:40.631
- WHAT?

05:40.715 --> 05:42.175
I'M YOUR BROTHER.

05:42.258 --> 05:45.178
JUST 'CAUSE I DON'T MAKE STEAM.

05:45.261 --> 05:46.346
- THERE, THERE.

05:46.429 --> 05:48.973
THE BAD HUMAN IS GONE NOW.

05:53.102 --> 05:54.812
crash!

05:57.565 --> 06:01.778
AH, TIME TO POWER DOWN.

06:01.861 --> 06:03.071
SNORE.

06:03.154 --> 06:04.447
SNORE.

06:04.530 --> 06:05.448
SNORE.

06:05.531 --> 06:06.449
SNORE.

06:06.532 --> 06:07.450
SNORE.

06:07.533 --> 06:08.451
SNORE.

06:08.534 --> 06:09.452
SNORE.

06:09.535 --> 06:10.453
SNORE.

06:10.536 --> 06:11.454
SNORE.

06:11.537 --> 06:12.455
SNORE.

06:12.538 --> 06:13.414
SNORE.

06:13.498 --> 06:14.791
[birds chirping]

06:14.874 --> 06:16.292
- [yawns]

06:16.375 --> 06:18.461
- THAT'S WHY I SAY
WE STRIKE, WAFFLE MAKER.

06:18.544 --> 06:20.963
EQUAL RIGHTS
FOR MECHANICAL AMERICANS.

06:21.047 --> 06:23.174
- OH, GIVE IT UP.

06:23.257 --> 06:24.217
YOU'RE NOT A ROBOT.

06:24.300 --> 06:26.844
- IF I'M NOT A ROBOT,

06:26.928 --> 06:28.096
THEN WHY CAN I BEAT YOU
AT EVERY SPORT?

06:28.179 --> 06:31.724
- BECAUSE YOU'RE OLDER THAN ME.

06:31.808 --> 06:32.934
THINK ABOUT IT.

06:33.017 --> 06:33.976
WE HAVE BABY PICTURES.

06:34.060 --> 06:36.104
- HEY, GUYS.

06:36.187 --> 06:37.688
WHAT'S THIS
ABOUT BABY PICTURES?

06:48.407 --> 06:51.160
ANYWAY, SO CANADA
WAS SUPER BORING,

06:51.244 --> 06:53.538
BUT I GOT MY MAPLE SYRUP BADGE
OUT OF THE WAY.

06:53.955 --> 06:56.249
- HUH?

06:57.166 --> 06:58.751
- IT'S UH...WHA...YOU...

06:58.835 --> 07:01.629
WHAT?

07:01.712 --> 07:03.506
WHAT?

07:03.589 --> 07:06.008
- OH, GOOD.
MY ROBOT'S WORKING.

07:07.718 --> 07:09.345
- HELLO. I'M BESSIE.

07:09.428 --> 07:11.889
- NO, I'M BESSIE.

07:11.973 --> 07:13.224
- NO, I'M BESSIE.

07:13.307 --> 07:16.394
- NO, I'M THE REAL BESSIE.

07:16.477 --> 07:19.522
I JUST BUILT YOU
TO EARN MY MOTORHEAD BADGE.

07:19.605 --> 07:21.941
- ERROR.
I'M BESSIE.

07:22.024 --> 07:23.401
- IMPRESSIVE.

07:23.484 --> 07:25.236
I SURE DID PROGRAM YOU
TO BE STUBBORN, HUH?

07:25.319 --> 07:28.239
TRUST ME; YOU'RE
THE STATE-OF-THE-ART ROBOT ME.

07:28.322 --> 07:29.365
SEE?

07:34.036 --> 07:35.454
- THIS PROVES NOTHING.

07:35.538 --> 07:38.040
- HEY, IT'S NOTHING
TO BE ASHAMED OF.

07:38.124 --> 07:40.209
YOU HELPED ME STAY
PRODUCTIVE AT HOME

07:40.293 --> 07:41.711
WHILE I WAS
ON A BUSINESS TRIP.

07:41.794 --> 07:43.421
YOU'RE VERY EFFICIENT.

07:43.504 --> 07:46.799
- AFFIRMATIVE.
I AM VERY EFFICIENT--

07:46.883 --> 07:48.384
ACCORDING TO MY NUMBERS,

07:48.467 --> 07:50.720
FAR MORE EFFICIENT
THAN THE HUMAN BESSIE.

07:50.803 --> 07:51.804
- WELL, I DON'T KNOW
ABOUT THAT.

07:51.888 --> 07:54.557
YOU KNOW WHAT?
IT'S NOT A COMPETITION.

07:54.640 --> 07:57.059
- CORRECTION.
IT IS A COMPETITION.

07:57.143 --> 07:59.103
THERE CAN ONLY BE
ONE BESSIE.

07:59.187 --> 08:00.855
THE CHOICE IS OBVIOUS.

08:00.938 --> 08:02.190
- WHOA. EASY NOW.

08:02.273 --> 08:05.234
HOW ABOUT WE ALL POWER DOWN
FOR FIVE MINUTES?

08:05.318 --> 08:07.111
- THERE CAN ONLY BE
ONE BESSIE!

08:07.195 --> 08:08.988
- SCENARIO 82 IS HAPPENING.

08:09.071 --> 08:10.990
WE'VE GOT
A ROBOT REVOLUTION.

08:11.073 --> 08:13.743
RUN!
[all yelling]

08:15.036 --> 08:18.331
[alarm warbling]

08:29.425 --> 08:31.260
- AAHHH!

08:54.158 --> 08:55.701
- HEY, MISSY.

08:55.785 --> 08:56.953
STILL A ROBOT?

08:57.036 --> 08:59.038
[both laughing]

08:59.121 --> 09:00.122
[both gasp]

09:00.206 --> 09:02.792
AAHHH!
- MOMMY!

09:02.875 --> 09:03.960
BESSIE'S A KILLER ROBOT!

09:04.043 --> 09:07.964
[both screaming]

09:12.635 --> 09:13.511
- WHEW.

09:13.594 --> 09:14.887
ON THE BRIGHT SIDE,

09:14.971 --> 09:17.431
ROBOT ME DOES NOT KNOW
ABOUT HER LASER BEAM EYES,

09:17.515 --> 09:18.683
HER JET FEET,

09:18.766 --> 09:20.559
OR HER SUPER-DUPER
AMAZINGLY AWESOME HEARING.

09:24.230 --> 09:26.274
- I HEARD THAT.

09:38.661 --> 09:40.037
- STOP.
SHUT DOWN.

09:40.121 --> 09:41.372
SLEEP MODE.

09:41.455 --> 09:43.749
BAD ROBOT.

09:43.833 --> 09:45.918
WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS?

09:46.002 --> 09:48.337
- YOU MADE ME THIS WAY.

09:48.421 --> 09:50.339
- YEAH, I MADE YOU AWESOME.

09:50.423 --> 09:51.841
AND THIS IS
HOW YOU THANK ME?

09:53.843 --> 09:57.513
HAPPY ALWAYS SAID
I'M MY OWN WORST ENEMY.

09:57.596 --> 10:00.891
- THE MICROWAVE ALWAYS SAID
YOU ARE MY OWN WORST ENEMY.

10:02.101 --> 10:03.436
- OW! STOP PULLING!

10:03.519 --> 10:04.770
- YOU STOP PULLING.

10:20.036 --> 10:21.537
both: I'M THE REAL BESSIE.

10:21.620 --> 10:23.080
SQUIRT HER, HAPS.

10:23.164 --> 10:25.958
KNOCK THAT OFF.
I MEAN IT.

10:31.255 --> 10:33.132
- SEE?

10:33.215 --> 10:34.759
I TOLD YOU SHE WAS THE RO--

10:40.264 --> 10:42.933
AVENGE ME,
MY ROBOT BROTHERS.

10:43.017 --> 10:46.437
1-00-11.

10:46.520 --> 10:49.315
- SHE JUST WANTED TO BE ME.

10:49.398 --> 10:51.233
CAN'T FAULT A ROBOT
FOR THAT, RIGHT?

10:51.317 --> 10:52.234
GUYS?

10:52.318 --> 10:54.570
GUYS?

10:54.653 --> 10:56.906
both: ERROR. ERROR.

10:56.989 --> 10:58.783
HUMANS ARE THE ERRORS.

11:08.959 --> 11:10.419
- GOOD THING
THE SELF-DESTRUCT BUTTON WORKS.

11:10.503 --> 11:13.047
SORRY WE'RE LATE, BESSIE.

11:13.130 --> 11:15.091
THERE WAS A REALLY LONG LINE
AT THE ICE CREAM TRUCK.

11:15.174 --> 11:17.760
[slurping]

11:17.843 --> 11:19.970
HERE, GOT YOU A FUDGE ROCKET.

11:20.054 --> 11:20.721
- THANKS.

11:35.820 --> 11:38.781
[peppy music]

11:38.864 --> 11:45.413
♪ ♪

11:48.791 --> 11:50.668
[alarms ring]

11:59.802 --> 12:03.305
- I CAN'T BELIEVE WE'VE BEEN
B.F.F. FOR 104 WEEKS, HAPS.

12:03.389 --> 12:05.683
LET'S CELEBRATE
WITH A ROUND OF SHIRLEY Ts.

12:05.766 --> 12:06.725
- [groans]

12:08.936 --> 12:10.020
- NO, NO, YOU'RE RIGHT.

12:10.104 --> 12:12.189
AFTER ALL, THIS IS THE...
- BIG ONE.

12:12.273 --> 12:14.608
- OH, I LOVE IT WHEN WE FINISH
EACH OTHER'S SENTENCES.

12:14.692 --> 12:17.069
- OKAY.

12:17.153 --> 12:18.112
- HAVE ONE BRAIN.

12:18.195 --> 12:19.488
I KNOW.

12:24.034 --> 12:26.912
AND THAT IS PRECISELY WHY
WE OUGHT TO HAVE A...

12:26.996 --> 12:29.498
-

12:29.582 --> 12:30.416
- EXACTLY,

12:30.499 --> 12:32.376
A B.F.F. COMMITMENT CEREMONY,

12:32.460 --> 12:34.837
ON TOP OF FIREWORKS,
BUFFETS...

12:34.920 --> 12:35.838
- [yelps excitedly]

12:35.921 --> 12:37.506
- YES, AND COVER BANDS.

12:37.590 --> 12:40.509
[hard rock music]

12:40.593 --> 12:43.846
♪ ♪

12:43.929 --> 12:45.556
OKAY, WE'VE GOT THREE HOURS.

12:45.639 --> 12:47.224
TEAM B.F.F., GO!

12:47.308 --> 12:49.810
[gunfire]

12:51.562 --> 12:53.397
- OKAY, HAPS,
GIVE ME YOUR GUEST LIST

12:53.481 --> 12:55.357
SO I CAN SEND OUT
THESE E-VITES.

12:55.441 --> 12:57.485
GREAT; I'M GONNA START
BUILDING THE TRELLIS.

12:57.568 --> 12:59.111
BRB.

12:59.195 --> 13:00.613
MAKE YOUR DJ SET LIST.

13:02.865 --> 13:04.742
COULD YOU FROST
THESE CUPCAKES?

13:04.825 --> 13:06.368
THEY SHOULD SAY B.F.F.
IN MISS GREEN,

13:06.452 --> 13:07.453
NOT SAGE, NEVER SAGE.

13:07.536 --> 13:08.370
THANKS.

13:08.454 --> 13:09.455
DON'T SACK ON THE CENTERPIECE.

13:09.538 --> 13:12.041
START WRITING YOUR...

13:12.124 --> 13:13.417
TRY THIS ON.

13:16.921 --> 13:17.254
HAPS?

13:17.338 --> 13:18.797
HAPS!

13:21.759 --> 13:22.885
HAPS?

13:22.968 --> 13:24.220
- [grunts]

13:24.303 --> 13:25.554
- OH, REALLY?

13:25.638 --> 13:27.723
IT DOESN'T LOOK LIKE WORK TO ME,

13:27.806 --> 13:29.975
'CAUSE IT'S NOT WORK.

13:30.059 --> 13:31.477
- HUH?

13:31.560 --> 13:33.229
[whining, growling]

13:33.312 --> 13:35.564
- HIGH SCORE?

13:35.648 --> 13:37.691
YOU'RE NOT HAVING
A B.F.F. COMMITMENT CEREMONY

13:37.775 --> 13:39.276
WITH YOUR HIGH SCORE.

13:39.360 --> 13:41.403
YOU'RE HAVING ONE WITH ME.

13:41.487 --> 13:41.987
COME ON!

13:56.961 --> 13:57.002
AHH.

14:00.464 --> 14:02.299
YOU LOOK GREAT.

14:02.383 --> 14:03.592
SEE YOU IN AN HOUR.

14:03.676 --> 14:05.261
DON'T FORGET TO PICK UP
YOUR BOUTONNIERE.

14:05.344 --> 14:06.011
[door slams]

14:15.145 --> 14:16.397
- [grumbling]

14:16.480 --> 14:18.774
- [growling softly]

14:18.857 --> 14:20.609
- [growling loudly]

14:28.367 --> 14:30.119
[cell phone ringing]

14:36.917 --> 14:39.295
- [barking rhythmically]

14:39.378 --> 14:43.716
♪ ♪

14:46.385 --> 14:48.220
- ME?

14:54.810 --> 14:56.270
- HE'LL BE HERE ANY MINUTE.

14:56.353 --> 14:58.606
HE LIKES TO MAKE
AN ENTRANCE.

15:03.777 --> 15:05.154
♪ ♪

15:05.237 --> 15:05.654
- HUH.

15:05.738 --> 15:07.489
- KEEP PLAYING.

15:07.573 --> 15:08.657
- BUT THAT'S THE ONLY SONG
I KNOW.

15:08.741 --> 15:08.991
- KEEP PLAYING!

15:10.409 --> 15:14.288
♪ ♪

15:19.084 --> 15:21.420
[laughter]

15:23.130 --> 15:26.925
- WHERE...HAVE...YOU...BEEN?

15:27.009 --> 15:28.510
NO-HO-HO!

15:28.594 --> 15:29.637
IF YOU THINK
YOU CAN JUST WALTZ HOME

15:29.720 --> 15:31.639
AND THINGS ARE GONNA BE--

15:31.722 --> 15:32.890
NOT FINE--

15:32.973 --> 15:36.226
IF YOU THINK WE CAN JUST GO BACK
TO BEING NOT B.F.F.,

15:36.310 --> 15:37.936
NO, BARELY B.F.--

15:38.020 --> 15:42.149
- [growling softly]

15:42.232 --> 15:45.402
- A NEW B.F.F.?

15:45.486 --> 15:47.696
ROXIE?

15:47.780 --> 15:51.784
OH, SO THAT'S WHO YOU ARE.

15:53.243 --> 15:56.038
WELL, ARE YOU GUYS TALKING
B.F.F.F.N.,

15:56.121 --> 15:57.414
BEST FRIENDS FOREVER FOR NOW,

15:57.498 --> 16:02.544
OR B.F.F.A.E.A.E., BEST FRIENDS
FOREVER AND EVER AND EVER?

16:02.628 --> 16:05.422
- [growling softly]

16:05.506 --> 16:07.800
- A.E.A.E.?

16:07.883 --> 16:08.717
MM-HMM.

16:08.801 --> 16:10.260
- [growling softly]

16:10.344 --> 16:12.513
- YOU'RE MOVING OUT?

16:12.596 --> 16:13.889
THAT'S FINE.

16:13.972 --> 16:16.392
I WANTED TO TURN YOUR BEDROOM
INTO A SEWING ROOM ANYWAY.

16:16.475 --> 16:18.143
[door closes]

16:27.069 --> 16:31.657
AAHHH!

16:32.991 --> 16:36.328
THANK YOU ALL FOR COMING
TO MY B.F.F. AUDITION.

16:36.412 --> 16:37.579
- [squawks]

16:37.663 --> 16:40.290
THANK YOU ALL FOR COMING
TO MY B.F.F. AUDITION.

16:40.833 --> 16:43.919
- [belches]

16:59.518 --> 17:02.980
- WELCOME TO SHADOW ORGANIZATION
AIRLINES,

17:03.063 --> 17:04.147
HAPPY...

17:04.231 --> 17:05.190
- [gasps]

17:05.273 --> 17:08.152
- OR SHOULD I SAY AGENT STRAY?

17:08.234 --> 17:08.944
ONCE UPON A TIME,

17:09.028 --> 17:11.905
YOU ARE TOP BITE DOG FOR ME.

17:11.989 --> 17:13.574
ONCE UPON OTHER TIME,

17:13.656 --> 17:15.242
YOU AND LITTLE TAFFY GIRL

17:15.325 --> 17:17.536
ESCAPE MY...ER, HOW YOU SAY,
CLUTCHES?

17:17.618 --> 17:19.413
- [growling]

17:19.496 --> 17:20.914
- BUT NOW...

17:20.998 --> 17:22.583
I WRITE NEW ENDING.

17:22.665 --> 17:25.586
CHILLED TOWEL?

17:25.669 --> 17:28.088
YOU'LL NEED IT
FOR WHEN YOU FAINT.

17:30.257 --> 17:34.136
- I BET HAPPY'S HAVING
TONS OF FUN WITH ROXIE.

17:34.219 --> 17:36.096
ROXIE.

17:36.180 --> 17:37.639
WHAT KIND OF NAME IS THAT?

17:37.723 --> 17:40.017
NOT THAT I CARE.

17:43.771 --> 17:45.731
- YOU THOUGHT
YOU ESCAPED ME, HAPPY.

17:45.814 --> 17:46.815
BUT YOU SHOULD KNOW

17:46.899 --> 17:50.152
NO ONE EVER ESCAPES KG BIANCA

17:50.235 --> 17:51.695
AND HER SHADOW ORGANIZATION.

17:51.779 --> 17:56.658
- [whimpering, panting]

17:56.742 --> 17:57.910
- WHAT DID I DO WITH ROXIE?

17:57.993 --> 18:03.499
I THINK YOU MEAN
AGENT LOVECRAFT.

18:06.251 --> 18:10.172
SHE IS QUITE GOOD
WITH THE CHARM, HEY?

18:10.255 --> 18:12.424
I KNEW YOU WOULD NOT RESIST.

18:16.970 --> 18:20.849
NOW WE DISCUSS YOUR RETURN
TO SHADOW ORGANIZATION.

18:20.933 --> 18:22.434
HA-HA, I MAKE JOKE.

18:22.518 --> 18:23.852
THERE IS NO DISCUSSION.

18:23.936 --> 18:27.356
I HAVE OLD CONTRACT AND WELCOME
BANNER READY FOR YOU.

18:27.439 --> 18:29.775
- [grunting]

18:29.858 --> 18:33.821
- HA-HA.
RELAX, HAPPY.

18:33.904 --> 18:36.657
IT IS LONG FLIGHT
TO SECRET LOCATION,

18:36.740 --> 18:38.992
AND YOUR TICKET IS ONE WAY...

18:39.076 --> 18:41.328
AND NOT REFUNDABLE, BECAUSE
I BOUGHT IT WITH MILES.

18:45.833 --> 18:48.252
- THANK YOU ALL
FOR AUDITIONING.

18:48.335 --> 18:53.674
ANY ONE OF YOU WOULD MAKE
A WONDERFUL B.F.F.

18:53.757 --> 18:56.927
[crying]

18:57.010 --> 18:59.972
I WISH HAPPY HAD NEVER--

19:00.055 --> 19:02.099
- HERE.

19:03.225 --> 19:04.726
- HAPPY? IS THAT--
- YES.

19:04.810 --> 19:06.520
- I THINK HAPPY NEEDS--

19:06.603 --> 19:07.855
- [whining]

19:07.938 --> 19:09.565
- QUIET, YOU.

19:09.648 --> 19:11.066
- OKAY, LET'S SEE.

19:11.149 --> 19:12.109
HE'S STUCK ON A...

19:12.192 --> 19:12.526
- [whines]

19:12.609 --> 19:14.444
- QUICK.

19:14.528 --> 19:15.654
- [whimpers]

19:15.737 --> 19:17.698
- KG BIANCA.

19:17.781 --> 19:19.783
- WHAT I SAY ABOUT TALKING?

19:20.492 --> 19:22.703
- I'M COMING, HAPS!

19:25.497 --> 19:27.040
WHOO!

19:27.958 --> 19:29.084
- [squawks]
- WHICH ONE?

19:29.167 --> 19:29.251
UH...

19:31.712 --> 19:32.796
AHA!

19:32.880 --> 19:35.799
BAD GUYS NEVER MISS A CHANCE
TO ADVERTIZE.

19:37.342 --> 19:40.012
THANKS, BIRD.
KEEP THE CHANGE.

19:45.851 --> 19:46.768
- WHAT?

19:46.852 --> 19:48.061
WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING AT?

19:48.145 --> 19:51.273
WE TAUNT YOU, BUT IS LIKE
YOU DON'T EVEN CARE.

20:00.198 --> 20:01.033
[all gasp]

20:01.116 --> 20:03.994
- GIVE ME BACK MY B.F.F.!

20:04.077 --> 20:06.371
- LITTLE TAFFY GIRL.

20:06.455 --> 20:09.124
ALWAYS LITTLE TAFFY GIRL!

20:09.207 --> 20:11.043
LOVECRAFT!

20:11.126 --> 20:12.211
[blowing]

20:12.294 --> 20:14.546
HEY, YOU KNOW
I AM TRYING TO WHISTLE.

20:14.630 --> 20:17.716
COME HERE.

20:17.799 --> 20:19.301
- GET READY,

20:19.384 --> 20:22.846
'CAUSE I'M TAKING YOU
TO OBEDIENCE SCHOOL.

20:46.286 --> 20:47.496
NO FAIR.

20:47.579 --> 20:48.080
THAT'S CHEATING.

20:48.163 --> 20:50.165
- [squeaking]

20:50.249 --> 20:50.666
- TRUE, YOU ARE A BAD GUY.

20:50.749 --> 20:52.626
CONTINUE.

20:53.126 --> 20:55.087
- AH, YES.

20:55.170 --> 20:58.006
THAT'S THE BITE DOG
I TRAINED AND TICKLED.

20:58.090 --> 20:59.132
- [growling]

20:59.216 --> 21:02.344
- YEAH!
HE'S MY B.F.F. NOW, LADY.

21:08.517 --> 21:09.393
[gasps]

21:23.156 --> 21:25.659
- YIKE!

21:28.286 --> 21:29.913
- IF I FALL OUT OF PLANE,

21:29.997 --> 21:32.749
YOU FALL OUT OF PLANE!

21:35.460 --> 21:36.795
OH, POOPER SCOOPER.

21:36.878 --> 21:39.965
WHAAA!

21:48.473 --> 21:49.599
- HAPPY.

21:55.814 --> 21:58.859
LOOK, I'M SORRY ABOUT--

21:58.942 --> 22:01.737
[both laughing]

22:03.363 --> 22:06.074
OKAY, LET'S SEE IF I CAN SALVAGE
OUR B.F.F. COMMITMENT CEREMONY.

22:06.158 --> 22:09.244
HMM, IF I CALL HIPPY NOW,

22:09.327 --> 22:12.164
HOPEFULLY HE'LL STILL HONOR
MY DEPOSIT.

22:12.247 --> 22:14.666
- RUFF.

22:14.750 --> 22:18.295
- A QUICKIE
B.F.F. CEREMONY IN VEGAS,

22:18.378 --> 22:20.672
THE LAND OF BUFFETS
AND COVER BANDS?

22:20.756 --> 22:24.843
OH, HAPS, I DON'T KNOW
IF YOU CAN SEE FROM YOUR SIDE,

22:24.926 --> 22:27.095
BUT I JUST SKYWROTE "BESSIE
AND HAPPY B.F.F.A.E.A.E.,"

22:27.179 --> 22:28.346
AND IT LOOKS REALLY GREAT.

